The scripts are run locally on the Hyper-V server from a remote desktop c
onnection:

1. getVMs.ps1 - prints a list of VMs (powered-on and powered-off VMs) on the 
Hyper-V server

2. shutdownVM.ps1 - shutsdown the VM; if the VM name is not passed in as an 
argument, it will prompt you for the name of the VM

3. startVM.ps1 - starts the VM; if the VM name is not passed in as an argument, 
it will prompt you for the sname of the VM
